Package com.camerontec.catalys.core.message

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IFIXMessage
    Interface which must be supported by all message objects processed by Catalys.
    IFIXMessageFactory
    Interface for factories of IFIXMessage.
    IFIXMessageSpecifics
    Defines the FIX specific methods in IFIXMessage - ie all methods which do not appear in the generic ITagValues interface, or in IFIXMessage itself.
    IFromMessageTransformer
    Transformer for converting IFIXMessage's into some other form.
    IMessageTransformer
    Transformer for converting objects into IFIXMessages or IFIXMessages into objects.
    IOrderedFIXMessageFactory
    A FIX message factory which is associated with an tag ordering registry and logic for mapping message types to ordering record ID's.
    ISendingTransformer
    Transformer for converting IFIXMessage's into a form suitable for sending over the wire.
    ISmartFIXMessageFactory
    Message factory that creates messages from existing data such as order requests or current order state.
    IToMessageTransformer
    Transformer for converting objects into IFIXMessages.

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    AbstractMessageException
    Abstract base class for exceptions that are thrown in the context of a FIX message, allowing values related to the message to be captured.
    MessageException
    Indicates that a problem was detected with the content or format of a Message.
    MessageIntegrityException
    Indicates that a problem was detected during the integrity check of FIX message.
    MessageParsingException
    Indicates that a problem was detected during the parsing of a FIX message from raw bytes.
